ample. Ultimately, X-ray spectral analysis of the\nNuSTAR sources is required to break this degeneracy between the distribution of\nabsorbing column densities and the strength of the Compton reflection component\nand thus refine our measurements of the XLF. Furthermore, the models that\nsuccessfully describe the high-redshift population seen by NuSTAR tend to\nover-predict previous, high-energy measurements of the local XLF, indicating\nthat there is evolution of the AGN population that is not fully captured by the\ncurrent models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 Nov 2015 06:42:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-16"}
