12 to be strongly depleted in carbon. We find evidence of non-LTE\neffects on the line strength of some ionic species such as Si II and Ni II. The\nmetallic abundances indicate that the star is metal-poor, with an abundance\npattern most likely produced by diffusion effects.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 Nov 2015 15:42:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 3 Dec 2015 09:41:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-06"}
